results.notes:
Some missing data probably will never permit to identify the lichen in this observation, but based on what I can see I will bet on Xanthoparmelia mougeotii, even taking into account that I not very familiar with the genus Xanthoparmelia. At least I think that it matches the short description given in the reference for that species.
The missing data are, for instance, details about the underside though the photos seem to indicate a dark color and the existence of rhizines. Other missing data are the chemical reactions on medulla. Even the data from the upper cortex are not complete, the C reaction is missing and I could not find it in the photos I took (which probably means C-). Note that the KC reaction exhibit some orange/red tones superimposed to the dark cortex at the place were it was made.

results.notes:
I return to the place of Observation MO77763 and looked for more specimens. I found some in the trees around. I decided to enlarge the place to observe and, about 150 meter from the original place, I found another specimen in a shrub already cutted. I believe that is of the same genus, but there are some differences, namely:
- In the color of thallus, the new one being more greyish, and the apothecia have no pinkish tones, with discs slightly darker;
- Concerning microscopy, the asci are shorter in general and with various forms, in contrast with the original specimen where the shape was regular. In addition it seems that there are less spores/ascus and that the spores are bigger.
